query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `symptoms` (
  `id` int AUTO_INCREMENT NOT NULL,
  `name_en` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `name_ar` varchar(255),
  `local_name` varchar(255),
  `category` varchar(100),
  `description` text,
  `severity_indicators` text,
  `associated_conditions` text,
  `red_flag_symptom` boolean DEFAULT false,
  `urgency_level` enum('immediate','urgent','routine'),
  `common_in_iraq` boolean DEFAULT true,
  `created_at` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updated_at` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  CONSTRAINT `symptoms_id` PRIMARY KEY(`id`)
);
